{"id": "393", "instruction": "We now define an algorithm: The definition of a(n) is the Doudna sequence: write n-1 in binary; the power of the k-th prime in a(n) is the number of 1's in the binary representation of n-1 that are followed by k-1 consecutive 0's. Given the input x_list (a series of values): [58, 59, 60, 61, 62, 63, 64, 65, 66, 67], determine the corresponding output sequence y_list.\n\nOptions:\nA. [250, 375, 108, 625, 162, 243, 64, 17, 26, 39]\nB. [255, 380, 110, 630, 164, 245, 67, 19, 28, 41]\nC. [251, 376, 109, 626, 163, 244, 65, 18, 27, 40]\nD. [270, 395, 125, 650, 175, 260, 80, 30, 36, 55]\nE. [265, 390, 120, 645, 170, 255, 75, 25, 34, 50]\nF. [240, 360, 102, 610, 155, 235, 59, 14, 20, 35]\nG. [245, 365, 106, 615, 159, 239, 60, 15, 23, 36]\nH. [260, 385, 115, 640, 169, 250, 72, 24, 32, 48]\nI. [249, 370, 107, 620, 160, 240, 63, 16, 25, 38]\nJ. [255, 378, 113, 635, 167, 248, 70, 22, 30, 45]", "output": "A"}
